            {
                "s2_paper_id": "eb63d4e8b294704e22e33f1d937812433a0dbac3",
                "title": "AVERAGES OF TWISTED $L$-FUNCTIONS",
                "year": 2012,
                "venue": "Journal of the Australian Mathematical Society",
                "citation_count": 9,
                "reference_count": 27,
                "abstract": "We use a relative trace formula on $\\text{GL}(2)$ to compute a sum of twisted modular $L$-functions anywhere in the critical strip, weighted by a Fourier coefficient and a Hecke eigenvalue. When the weight $k$ or level $N$ is sufficiently large, the sum is nonzero. Specializing to the central point, we show in some cases that the resulting bound for the average is as good as that predicted by the Lindel\u00f6f hypothesis in the $k$ and $N$ aspects.",
